-- Mauritian Exchange Says it Plans to Offer Trading in Naira and Shillings
-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 2010-10-18T07:00:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-18/mauritian-exchange-says-it-plans-to-offer-trading-in-naira-and-shillings.html
Mauritius’s commodity and currency
exchange will start trading in Nigeria’s naira and the Kenyan
and Ugandan shillings against the dollar within six months, its
chief executive officer said.  The Global Board of Trade Ltd., which begins operations
today, offers contracts in gold, silver, the Mauritian rupee,
the South African rand, the pound and the yen to the dollar,
Joseph Bosco said in an interview on Oct. 16 in Balaclava, north
of the capital, Port Louis.  The  State Bank of India , Mauritius’s Banque des
Mascareignes and  Barclays Plc  will be the clearing houses for
the exchange. It is owned by  Financial Technologies (India) Ltd .  The exchange cost $50 million to set up and will require
another $50 million in investment, Bosco said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
